 and meticulous research, the book sheds light on the intricate workings of our digitised economy. Staab's compelling analysis challenges us to confront the realities of surveillance capitalism and the urgent need to address the inequities it perpetuates.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / Theory.2bisacsh  aAmazon.  aApple.  aGoogle.  aMarxism.  aPlatform Capitalism.  aSchumpeter.  aTencent.  aZuboff.  aalgorithmic management.  adigital capitalism.  adigital inequality.  ameta-platform.  aplatform economy.  aproprietary markets.  atechno-economy.  aventure capital.1 aStaab, Philipp, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packagez9783111206455oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152617217440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526172174423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526172174/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPb2023